                            <comment id="17458126" author="ajisakaa" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2021 02:00:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;After reverting &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-18034&quot; title=&quot;Bump mina-core from 2.0.16 to 2.1.5 in /hadoop-project &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-18034&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-18034&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the test passed. However, now I don&apos;t think reverting is the right way. I&apos;ll investigate what is the root cause and how to fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17458129" author="ajisakaa" created="Mon, 13 Dec 2021 02:17:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I ran the test with several mina-core versions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2.1.5: NG (CVE-2021-41973 fixed)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2.1.0: NG&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2.0.22: OK (CVE-2021-41973 fixed)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2.0.16: OK&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I think 2.0.22 is a good choice. In addition, we should consider upgrading sshd-core because mina-core is used by sshd-core.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
